$ Graphviz: node
@ node

The shape of a node can be specified with the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/shape[`shape`] → tools/Graphviz/attributes[attribute].

There are three *main types* of nodes:
  • → tools/Graphviz/elems/node/main-types/polygon-based[Polygon based]
  • → tools/Graphviz/elems/node/main-types/record-based[Record based]
  • User defined

{ Default attributes

  The default → tools/Graphviz/attributes[attributes] for nodes are `shape=ellipse, width=.75, height=.5 label="\N"`:

  The default value `"\N"` a node's → tools/Graphviz/attributes/label[`label`] attribute causes the label (that is: the text within the node) to be the name of the node.
 (See the the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/types/escString[`escString` type].)


  gh|about-Graphviz|/elems/node/default-attributes.dot||

  gh|about-Graphviz|/elems/node/img/default-attributes.png||

}
{ Filled nodes #graphviz-filled-nodes

  In order to produce a node that is filled with a (background-)color, it needs to have the two → tools/Graphviz/attributes[attributes]
    • → tools/Graphviz/attributes/style[`style=filled`] and
    • → tools/Graphviz/attributes/fillcolor[`fillcolor`]

  gh|about-Graphviz|/elems/node/filled.dot||
  gh|about-Graphviz|/elems/node/img/filled.png||

}
{ Size of a node

  `→ tools/Graphviz/attributes/shape[shape]=plain` is shorthand for `shape=none width=0 height=0 margin=0`. This enforces that the size of the node is determined by its
  → tools/Graphviz/attributes/label[`label`].

}

